<!-- WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE
Pre-Android 10 (API level 28):

This permission granted apps broad write access to the entire external storage (usually an SD card).
It was considered a risky permission as apps could potentially access and modify user data stored on the SD card.
Android 10 and Above (API level 29 and higher):

While the permission still exists, it no longer provides direct write access to the entire external storage due to Scoped Storage.
Instead, apps can only write to their own designated app-specific directory within the external storage.-->

